main event: A round object, color of fire, was observed as a flash in the sky off Goose AB, Newfoundland on 11 October 1956.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 15-20 minutes, The object was described as being the size of a window of an aircraft, Radar operators attempted visual sighting, but nothing was seen, The object was observed as straight down and down to the horizon, There is no photograph present in the report.
